Package: APIS
Type: Package
Title: APIS: An Auto-Adaptive Parentage Inference Software tolerant to missing parents
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Ronan GRIOT, François ALLAL, Romain MORVEZEN, Sophie BRARD-FUDULEA, Pierrick HAFFRAY, Florence PHOCAS and Marc VANDEPUTTE
Maintainer: Ronan GRIOT <ronan.griot@gmail.com>, François ALLAL <fallal@ifremer.fr>
Description: This package contains the R functions presented in Griot & al. (2019) to perform
    parentage assignment based on observed average Mendelian transmission probability distributions.
    The main function of this package is the function APIS, which is the parentage assignment function.
License: GPL
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Depends: doSNOW, foreach, ggplot2, gridExtra
Imports: doSNOW, foreach, ggplot2, gridExtra
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
